steps.instruction:
This will make 2 loafs  
Follow [this](https://www.kingarthurflour.com/blog/2019/10/14/rustic-sourdough-bread) for a more step by step guide

- Combine all the ingredients, knead to form a smooth dough
- Allow it to rise in a lightly greased and covered bowl till it has doubled in size (about 90 minutes)
- Gently git the dough in half
- Gently shape the dough into two ovals
    - For longer loaves, to 10 inch to 11 inch logs
- Place the loaves on a lightly greased or parchment paper lines baking sheet
- Cover and let rise until very puffy (about 1 hour)
    - Near the end of this step, preheat the oven to 425F
- Spray the loaves with the lukewarm water
- Make two fairly deep slashes in each loaf
- Bake them for 25 to 30 minutes or until very deeply golden brown
